So, how can you contribute?

141
00:08:27.807 --> 00:08:29.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That.
-Huh?

142
00:08:29.609 --> 00:08:32.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That rifle has a barrel
that is slightly bent.

143
00:08:32.111 --> 00:08:34.146  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So you should aim
a little bit to the left.

144
00:08:34.213 --> 00:08:36.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And that CO2 cartridge is loose.

145
00:08:36.649 --> 00:08:37.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tanaka] Huh.

146
00:08:37.950 --> 00:08:41.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Guess I know a little more about guns
and machines than Mr. Tanaka does.

147
00:08:42.088 --> 00:08:45.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Very good. Not bad at all.

148
00:08:46.592 --> 00:08:49.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, the game begins.

149
00:08:51.297 --> 00:08:53.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's a way out!

150
00:08:53.733 --> 00:08:56.168  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What'll we do when we get outside?

151
00:08:56.536 --> 00:08:58.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both grunting]

152
00:08:58.905 --> 00:09:02.041  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You just go and lead a normal life.

153
00:09:02.108 --> 00:09:04.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is no job for a kid.

154
00:09:05.144 --> 00:09:07.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Ko yells]

155
00:09:08.314 --> 00:09:09.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Damn!
-What do we do?

156
00:09:09.749 --> 00:09:10.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[door clangs]

157
00:09:11.884 --> 00:09:12.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Over there.

158
00:09:13.853 --> 00:09:16.756  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Jump. I'll buy some time.
-Huh?

159
00:09:17.557 --> 00:09:18.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
From here?

160
00:09:18.624 --> 00:09:21.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're an Ajin, right?
Now hurry up and jump.

161
00:09:21.260 --> 00:09:23.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I-- I'm afraid of heights.

162
00:09:23.896 --> 00:09:26.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now listen, those guys won't quit.

163
00:09:26.632 --> 00:09:29.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Even if the police
manage to get in their way,

164
00:09:29.101 --> 00:09:31.737  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
there's no telling how many people
they'll end up killing.

165
00:09:31.904 --> 00:09:33.172  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But what about you?

166
00:09:33.239 --> 00:09:36.943  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have a family out there,
a young daughter.

167
00:09:37.009 --> 00:09:39.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No matter what, I have to stop those guys.

168
00:09:40.246 --> 00:09:42.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Okay, then push me out.
-Huh?

169
00:09:42.582 --> 00:09:44.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't push a kid off the ledge.

170
00:09:44.216 --> 00:09:45.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshot]

171
00:09:45.585 --> 00:09:47.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Mister!
-Hey. We got them!

172
00:09:47.653 --> 00:09:49.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Tanaka. Go for it.

173
00:09:52.291 --> 00:09:53.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You really are a pretty bad shot.

174
00:09:53.926 --> 00:09:55.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aw, shut up.

175
00:09:55.328 --> 00:09:56.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[groaning]

176
00:09:58.931 --> 00:10:01.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Now it's up to you.
-Huh?

177
00:10:02.001 --> 00:10:05.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're the only one who can stop Sato now.

178
00:10:05.605 --> 00:10:06.606  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hold on.

179
00:10:06.672 --> 00:10:09.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You... You'll have to stop him.

180
00:10:10.009 --> 00:10:12.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now go!

181
00:10:12.244 --> 00:10:13.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Ko] Okay.

182
00:10:14.714 --> 00:10:17.083  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Tanaka] <i>A little to the left.</i>

183
00:10:20.319 --> 00:10:21.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

184
00:10:21.253 --> 00:10:22.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Mister!
-What?

185
00:10:29.328 --> 00:10:32.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hurry, go!

186
00:10:32.765 --> 00:10:33.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh...

187
00:10:33.866 --> 00:10:35.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right.

188
00:10:36.736 --> 00:10:38.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You gotta be kidding!

189
00:10:44.777 --> 00:10:48.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Sokabe] This is the TV footage taken
in front of the Ministry the other day.

190
00:10:51.117 --> 00:10:52.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This man here staggers unnaturally,

191
00:10:52.952 --> 00:10:55.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as though
he bumped into something we can't see.

192
00:10:56.122 --> 00:10:59.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh... So there was an IBM there.

193
00:10:59.291 --> 00:11:00.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

194
00:11:00.426 --> 00:11:02.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Although unfortunately
we can't tell how many.

195
00:11:02.395 --> 00:11:03.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Zoom in more.

196
00:11:03.829 --> 00:11:05.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's really nothing else to look at.

197
00:11:05.331 --> 00:11:07.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. That one back there.

198
00:11:10.836 --> 00:11:13.906  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's following something with his eyes.

199
00:11:14.673 --> 00:11:16.976  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He can see the IBM walk by.

200
00:11:18.177 --> 00:11:22.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's the one. He's our lead.

201
00:11:22.281 --> 00:11:24.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting and grunting]

202
00:11:27.219 --> 00:11:28.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[scoffs]

203
00:11:28.154 --> 00:11:31.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That little bastard sure can run,
can't he?

204
00:11:32.391 --> 00:11:34.026  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man in strained voice] Hey.

205
00:11:35.327 --> 00:11:40.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do you really think
that Sato's way is right?

206
00:11:42.301 --> 00:11:43.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that?

207
00:11:44.703 --> 00:11:48.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's just...
The government hides information

208
00:11:49.041 --> 00:11:53.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
probably just so they can avoid
creating a panic.

209
00:11:53.879 --> 00:11:58.084  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But if you start with this terrorism,

210
00:11:58.150 --> 00:12:03.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
things will get out of hand. [grunting]

211
00:12:04.190 --> 00:12:07.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The whole country will support...

212
00:12:08.160 --> 00:12:11.831  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
hunting down Ajins.

213
00:12:21.440 --> 00:12:23.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[woman on TV]
<i>When I go to bed, it's with you.</i>

214
00:12:24.376 --> 00:12:26.045  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

215
00:12:26.479 --> 00:12:28.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you really sure that it'll be okay?

216
00:12:28.914 --> 00:12:30.749  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Me staying here like this?

217
00:12:30.950 --> 00:12:34.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ah, it's fine. After all,
you not only carried me here,

218
00:12:34.186 --> 00:12:36.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but you brought my things in, too.

219
00:12:37.056 --> 00:12:39.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you so much.

220
00:12:40.226 --> 00:12:42.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] <i>She already saw my face, anyway.</i>

221
00:12:42.394 --> 00:12:45.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>This is less suspicious than running away.</i>

222
00:12:45.831 --> 00:12:47.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs] Here you are.

223
00:12:47.533 --> 00:12:50.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Sorry I don't have anything better
to offer.

224
00:12:51.170 --> 00:12:52.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[on TV] <i>And now for our next story.</i>

225
00:12:52.938 --> 00:12:54.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The search for Kei Nagai,</i>

226
00:12:54.340 --> 00:12:57.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>an Ajin who escaped</i>
<i>from the research facility three days ago,</i>

227
00:12:57.776 --> 00:12:58.777  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>is still underway.</i>

228
00:12:58.844 --> 00:13:03.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The police have increased their forces</i>
<i>and are asking for eyewitness accounts.</i>

229
00:13:03.482 --> 00:13:06.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>There has been a great deal of uproar</i>
<i>about Ajins lately,</i>

230
00:13:06.785 --> 00:13:10.523  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>with doubts about human experimentation</i>
<i>and the mysterious explosion.</i>

231
00:13:10.789 --> 00:13:12.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>What does the future hold?</i>

232
00:13:16.428 --> 00:13:19.131  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't plan on doing anything rash.

233
00:13:19.198 --> 00:13:22.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure every man has his own reasons,
anyway.

234
00:13:23.502 --> 00:13:25.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, you're called Kei?

235
00:13:26.205 --> 00:13:29.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have a grandson
just about the same age as you.

236
00:13:29.275 --> 00:13:33.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
His name is Ryota. Unfortunately,
I haven't seen him in years.

237
00:13:36.949 --> 00:13:38.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

238
00:13:54.833 --> 00:13:59.004  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kei] <i>This is perfect.</i>
<i>I can test out a few things.</i>

239
00:14:13.319 --> 00:14:15.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

240
00:14:15.221 --> 00:14:18.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh? Sato!

241
00:14:21.026 --> 00:14:24.330  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh? It's not him!

242
00:14:25.297 --> 00:14:26.599  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

243
00:14:28.467 --> 00:14:29.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

244
00:14:30.569 --> 00:14:32.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Ko] <i>Is that an Ajin?</i>

245
00:14:36.942 --> 00:14:41.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, that's not the direction Sato was.

246
00:14:43.582 --> 00:14:48.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, who is it, then?

247
00:14:55.127 --> 00:14:56.161  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

248
00:14:56.328 --> 00:14:58.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's gone already?

249
00:14:58.364 --> 00:15:01.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why does it disappear on its own
like that?

250
00:15:03.002 --> 00:15:04.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

251
00:15:05.204 --> 00:15:08.440  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kei] <i>But at least now I know</i>
<i>how to summon it.</i>

252
00:15:12.244 --> 00:15:17.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Kei IBM] Rescuing people
really isn't worth all the effort.

253
00:15:17.950 --> 00:15:19.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>This is the fifth one.</i>

254
00:15:20.052 --> 00:15:23.122  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I can summon it several times</i>
<i>in a row now.</i>

255
00:15:31.263 --> 00:15:33.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

256
00:15:35.935 --> 00:15:37.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

257
00:15:38.370 --> 00:15:40.005  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[yells]

258
00:15:40.472 --> 00:15:43.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh. Morning.

259
00:15:43.676 --> 00:15:45.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good morning. [chuckles]

260
00:15:46.612 --> 00:15:49.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, my. So much blood!

261
00:15:49.615 --> 00:15:52.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, this?
I just had a little fall earlier.

262
00:15:52.952 --> 00:15:55.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Stay still.
We need to call an ambulance.

263
00:15:55.454 --> 00:15:58.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-No, no, no, I'm fine. [chuckles]
-Oh, wait.

264
00:15:58.390 --> 00:16:00.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckling] I'm okay.

265
00:16:01.293 --> 00:16:02.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman] Wait.

266
00:16:02.261 --> 00:16:03.128  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman sighing]

267
00:16:12.705 --> 00:16:14.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

268
00:16:18.477 --> 00:16:21.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That old lady, so nosy.

269
00:16:22.214 --> 00:16:23.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

270
00:16:24.650 --> 00:16:26.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

271
00:16:26.318 --> 00:16:28.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I must have left it unlocked.

272
00:16:31.190 --> 00:16:32.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Huh?

273
00:16:33.659 --> 00:16:36.028  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're Ko Nakano, right?

274
00:16:36.095 --> 00:16:37.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is your place?

275
00:16:38.263 --> 00:16:41.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah. But I, uh...

276
00:16:45.037 --> 00:16:46.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunts]

277
00:16:46.171 --> 00:16:47.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Damn it!
[man] Don't let him get away!

278
00:16:49.408 --> 00:16:55.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Those guys in black are the same ones
who were at Dr. Ogura's location, right?

279
00:16:56.348 --> 00:16:57.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

280
00:16:57.282 --> 00:17:00.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Were they sent by the Ministry?
-No, of course they weren't.

281
00:17:01.553 --> 00:17:04.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>They were employed by a certain man.</i>

282
00:17:06.225 --> 00:17:09.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And then I decided
to recruit them for myself.

283
00:17:09.428 --> 00:17:14.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They do various jobs for me.
